{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Strobe",
  "description": "Strobe is a beat-synced brightness modulator, decomposed from the legacy fused kernel into two reusable pieces: a beat-gated square wave and a brightness flash effect.\n\nThe source image flows into the flash node, which modulates it by a brightness envelope driven by the beat gate. The beat gate reads FrameTime.beats and produces a square wave at a synced rate (1/1 to 1/64), scaled by the amount slider. The gate is held internally at 50 percent duty cycle and zero phase, giving a clean on/off pulse matching the legacy strobe behavior.\n\nThe flash node applies the gate signal to the image in one of three modes: Opacity fades toward black, White fades toward white, and Gain applies a 3x brighten. The result is driven directly to the output.\n\nNo grouping is needed: the graph is already transparent, and moving between nodes requires no layering.",
